Cimatron Surges to 3-Month High as Second-Quarter Profit Triples

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-08-04T14:03:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/cimatron-surges-to-3-month-high-as-second-quarter-profit-triples.html
Cimatron Ltd. soared to the highest
in more than three months after the maker of software for the
toolmaking and manufacturing industries reported second-quarter
profit that more than tripled.  The shares climbed 15 percent to 13.79 shekels at the 4:30
p.m. close in  Tel Aviv , the highest level since April 17, giving
the company a market value of 128.2 million shekels ($37
million).  Net income jumped to $881,000 from $278,000 a year earlier,
as revenue rose to $10 million from $8.4 million, the company
said today in a PR Newswire statement. Givat Shmuel, Israel-
based Cimatron declared a dividend of 0.80 shekel, or about 23
cents, a share payable Sept. 12 to shareholders of record Aug.
24.  To contact the reporter on this story:
